### English Title:
Fatima Hassouna, a journalist documenting the war, killed in an Israeli airstrike

### English Text Summary:
Fatima Hassouna, a journalist who covered the conflict in Gaza for 18 months, was killed in an Israeli airstrike along with seven family members. In a poignant Instagram post, she expressed her desire for a loud death that would resonate globally. The Israeli military claimed the strike targeted a Hamas militant. The Palestinian Journalists' Association reported that 212 journalists have been killed in Gaza since October 7, 2023, urging an international investigation. Hassouna's work highlighted the human toll of war, and she was featured in an upcoming documentary set to premiere at the Cannes Film Festival. Her death has sparked outrage and calls for accountability.

